  "prompt": "Does NASA recruit Indians?",
  "response": "Yes, NASA does recruit individuals from various countries, including India. NASA welcomes talented scientists, engineers, and researchers from around the world. Many Indian professionals have worked at NASA, both as NASA employees and through collaborations with international space agencies. Some key points:\n\n1. NASA has hired numerous Indian-origin scientists and engineers over the years.\n\n2. Indian professionals have made significant contributions to NASA's space exploration and research programs.\n\n3. To work at NASA, candidates typically need to:\n- Meet specific educational qualifications\n- Have relevant technical skills\n- Possess necessary work authorization (like citizenship or work visa)\n- Pass background checks\n- Meet specific job requirements\n\n4. NASA offers various opportunities including:\n- Civil service positions\n- Research positions\n- Contractor positions\n- Internships and fellowships\n\n5. Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO) also collaborates with NASA on various space research projects.\n\nWhile NASA primarily hires U.S. citizens for many positions due to security clearance requirements, they do have opportunities for international professionals, including those from India, particularly in research and specialized technical roles.\n\nInterested candidates should regularly check NASA's official careers website for current job openings and requirements.",
